# =========================================================================
# DEVELOPER DOCUMENTATION & NEXT STEPS
# =========================================================================
# The '.env' configuration is ignored to prevent database passwords
# and JWT tokens from being checked into the repository.
#
# To setup and run the backend locally:
#
# 1. Create a '.env' file in this '/backend' directory with:
#    PORT=5000
#    DB_HOST=127.0.0.1
#    DB_PORT=3306
#    DB_USER=root
#    DB_PASSWORD=Root@123
#    DB_NAME=store_rating_platform
#    JWT_SECRET=super_secret_store_rating_jwt_token_key_2026
#
# 2. Database Administration:
#    - MySQL server must be active on localhost:3306.
#    - User: root, Password: Root@123
#    - The database (store_rating_platform) is created automatically on start.
#
# 3. Start Backend:
#    - Run: npm install
#    - Run: npm run dev  (runs nodemon on port 5000)
#
# 4. Start Frontend:
#    - Navigate to '/frontend' folder.
#    - Run: npm install
#    - Run: npm run dev  (runs Vite on http://localhost:5173/)
# =========================================================================
